core:dwarf.description:
{green|Dwarf}

Because of their slowness, dwarves are perhaps best used to defend ranged attackers. Battle dwarves have greater mobility and are more versatile.

{gold|Special Ability : Magic resistance}
Dwarves have a 20% resistance to magic which gives them a chance to ignore the effects of hostile spell attacks.

core:battleDwarf.description:
{green|Battle Dwarf}

Because of their slowness, dwarves are perhaps best used to defend ranged attackers. Battle dwarves have greater mobility and are more versatile.

{gold|Special Ability : Magic resistance}
Dwarves have a 40% resistance to magic which gives them a chance to ignore the effects of hostile spell attacks.

core:grandElf.description:
{green|Grand Elf}

Armed with bows, elves are the only Rampart units with a ranged attacks.

{gold|Special Ability : Doube shoot}
Grand elves take two shots per attack.

core:pegasus.description:
{green|Pegasus}

Pegasi, winged horses ridden by female elven warriors, are the flying cavalry of the Rampart army. Their appearance on the battlefield makes it more difficult for enemy spellcasters, who must pay two extra spell points per spell cast when pegasi are present.

{gold|Special Ability : Magic damper}
Both Pegasi and Silver Pegasi have a magic damper special ability. It causes enemy hero's spells to cost two extra spell points, if pegasi were present at the beginning of the combat. Even if all the pegasi die during the battle, the spells will cost two extra points until the end of combat.

core:silverPegasus.description:
{green|Silver Pegasus}

